1932;;Make Me a Star;;American;;William Beaudine;;Joan Blondell, Stuart Erwin, ZaSu Pitts;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Make_Me_a_Star;;A small-town delivery boy Merton Gill (Stuart Erwin) arrives in Hollywood, bright-eyed and bushy-tailed and complete with a diploma from the National Correspondence Academy of Acting. Crashing the gates of Majestic Pictures Merton manages to fumble his one line bit in the latest Buck Benson (George Templeton) western and is fired on the spot.[2]